Eight Si detectors were placed in the chamber to
detect 17O ions elastically scattered from the Ti
foil at a 21 degree angle to monitor the beam
intensity with a precision better than 4%.
The c.m. energy resolution was 25 keV (full width at
half maximum) at zero degrees and deteriorated up to
60 keV with angles deviating from zero degrees.
